"title": "7115: children of God",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7115",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Israel and the church are the chief objects of God's fatherly love. People become God's children through faith and are then encouraged by Scripture to imitate their heavenly Father in their daily living.</p>\n<h2>Human beings as God's children</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:27\">GEN 1:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen6:2\">GEN 6:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen6:4\">GEN 6:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps82:6\">PSA 82:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal2:10\">MAL 2:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:38\">LUK 3:38</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph3:14\">EPH 3:14</a></p>\n<h2>Israel as God's children</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos11:1\">HOS 11:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod4:22-Exod4:23\">EXO 4:22–4:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps73:15\">PSA 73:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps80:15\">PSA 80:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa43:6\">ISA 43:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa63:16\">ISA 63:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:20\">JER 31:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom9:4\">ROM 9:4</a></p>\n<h3>Israel as God's rebellious children</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa1:2\">ISA 1:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut32:5\">DEU 32:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut32:20\">DEU 32:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa30:1\">ISA 30:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa30:9\">ISA 30:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer3:4-Jer3:5\">JER 3:4–3:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer4:22\">JER 4:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek20:21\">EZK 20:21</a></p>\n<h2>God's son</h2>\n<h3>Promises of God's son</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam7:12-2Sam7:14\">2SA 7:12–7:14</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr17:11-1Chr17:13\">1CH 17:11–17:13</a> <em>These words referred originally to David's son, Solomon, but in the NT they are applied to Jesus Christ.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr22:10\">1CH 22:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr28:6\">1CH 28:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps2:7\">PSA 2:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps89:26-Ps89:27\">PSA 89:26–89:27</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ as God's son</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:5\">HEB 1:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt3:17\">MAT 3:17</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:11\">MRK 1:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:22\">LUK 3:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:32\">LUK 1:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:33\">ACT 13:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:4\">ROM 1:4</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's followers as God's children</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:2\">MAT 9:2</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:5\">MRK 2:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:22\">MAT 9:22</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:34\">MRK 5:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:48\">LUK 8:48</a></p>\n<h2>Becoming God's children through faith in Jesus Christ</h2>\n<h3>Becoming God's children by new birth</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:12-John1:13\">JHN 1:12–1:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:36\">JHN 12:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom9:8\">ROM 9:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:26\">GAL 3:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John5:1\">1JN 5:1</a></p>\n<h3>Becoming God's children by adoption</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:5\">EPH 1:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:23\">ROM 8:23</a> <em>This adoption will be fully realised in the future</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:4-Gal4:5\">GAL 4:4–4:5</a></p>\n<h3>Becoming God's children by the Spirit</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:15\">ROM 8:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:6\">GAL 4:6</a></p>\n<h2>God's dealings with his children</h2>\n<h3>God loves his children</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:1\">1JN 3:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut1:31\">DEU 1:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps103:13\">PSA 103:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:1\">EPH 5:1</a></p>\n<h3>God disciplines his children</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut8:5\">DEU 8:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov3:11-Prov3:12\">PRO 3:11–3:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:5-Heb12:10\">HEB 12:5–12:10</a></p>\n<h3>God does not abandon his children</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos1:10\">HOS 1:10</a></strong> <em>God had previously (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos1:9\">Hos 1:9</a>) announced his judgment that Israel would be his people no longer.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut31:6\">DEU 31:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut31:8\">DEU 31:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh1:5\">JOS 1:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:5\">HEB 13:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:9\">JER 31:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal3:17\">MAL 3:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:24\">LUK 15:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom9:26\">ROM 9:26</a></p>\n<h2>Behaviour expected of God's children</h2>\n<h3>God's children imitate their heavenly Father</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:1\">EPH 5:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:48\">MAT 5:48</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:36\">LUK 6:36</a></p>\n<h3>God's children live by the Father's standards</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:15\">PHP 2:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev11:44-Lev11:45\">LEV 11:44–11:45</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut14:1-Deut14:2\">DEU 14:1–14:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:9\">MAT 5:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:44-Matt5:45\">MAT 5:44–5:45</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:35-Luke6:36\">LUK 6:35–6:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:14\">ROM 8:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor6:17-2Cor6:18\">2CO 6:17–6:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:14-1Pet1:16\">1PE 1:14–1:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:10\">1JN 3:10</a></p>\n<h2>The privileges and blessings of being God's children</h2>\n<h3>God's children are eternally secure</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:35\">JHN 8:35</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:16\">ROM 8:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:21\">ROM 8:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John5:19\">1JN 5:19</a></p>\n<h3>The needs of God's children are always supplied</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt7:9-Matt7:11\">MAT 7:9–7:11</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:11-Luke11:13\">LUK 11:11–11:13</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:25-Matt6:32\">MAT 6:25–6:32</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:22-Luke12:30\">LUK 12:22–12:30</a> <em>needs for the present life</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:36\">LUK 20:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:23\">ROM 8:23</a> <em>promises for the life to come</em></p>\n<h3>God's children have a sure inheritance</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:7\">REV 21:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer3:19\">JER 3:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:17-Rom8:19\">ROM 8:17–8:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:7\">GAL 4:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:2\">1JN 3:2</a></p>",
